requirements.details:
Create src/data/cv.ts extracting all CV data from ../cv-astro into a single typed file. Also copy the portrait image.

TypeScript interfaces:
- Job: { title: string, company: string, period: string, achievements: string[], consultancy?: string, buzzwords: string[] }
- Education: { degree: string, institution: string, period: string, details: string[] }
- TechCategory: { title: string, items: string[] }
- ContactInfo: { email: string, phone: string, address: { name: string, street: string, city: string }, website: string }

Exported data:
- contactInfo: ContactInfo = { email: 'jonaseriksson84@gmail.com', phone: '0704200175', address: { name: 'Jonas Eriksson', street: 'Ljusstöparbacken 22', city: '117 65 Stockholm' }, website: 'mynameisjonas.dev' }
- aboutText: string[] = [
    'Fullstack web developer with 13+ years of professional experience, specializing in frontend development and JavaScript/TypeScript. Extensive experience with backend and API development in Go, Python, Java, and Node.js.',
    'Strong team player with proven leadership experience, equally comfortable driving projects independently. Quick to adapt to new technologies and environments while maintaining focus on delivering high-quality results.'
  ]
- jobs: Job[] = [all 5 jobs from cv-astro Experience.astro]
- education: Education[] = [both entries from cv-astro Education.astro]
- techStack: TechCategory[] = [all 5 categories from cv-astro TechStack.astro]

Exported helper:
- getGroupedJobs(): Job[][] — groups jobs by consultancy (non-consultant jobs as single-item arrays, consultant jobs with same consultancy grouped together), same logic as cv-astro Experience.astro reduce()

Copy portrait:
- cp ../cv-astro/public/jonas2.jpg public/jonas.jpg
